parameters:
It seems like Lunaroa really likes this village... The village
chief is also kind.

I might understand Lunaroa's feelings a little. Maybe because
it's a little similar to Hatayaki Village.
(I wonder what she wants to convey.)

Ronoa, you know... She said, I'm glad to see you after such a
long time.

\SE[86]Yeah, they seemed really exhausted. \SE[83]They must have
been really tired.

\SE[82]That's true... \!\SE[51]But, we can't move forward until
they take a break...

\SE[74]I might end up being resented by those girls. \SE[75]I was
hoping we could get along...

\SE[91]Melissa and Lunaroa are both strong girls, so I'm sure
they'll understand. \!\SE[51]It might take some time though.

\SE[74]For those two, it's the second time they've lost their
home... \SE[67]It's pathetic how powerless I am...

\SE[95]That's... the same for me too... \SE[51]I couldn't do
anything...

\SE[85]If it's about reasons to fight... I have one. \SE[44]If I
can reduce even a little bit of this sadness... If there's
something I can do... \SM[nod]\SE[102]I want to help with that.

\SE[100]It might still be a half-hearted feeling... \!\SE[44]But
I... want to choose it.

\SE[95]Um, umm... I wonder if I said it well...? \SE[51]I'm not
confident in putting it into words...

\SE[72]No, my feelings were properly conveyed. \SE[51]...Thank
you, Laura.

\SE[85]Oh, did I wake up...? \!\SE[90]Sorry\. Was I being
noisy...?

\SE[85]Ah, Melissa woke up too? \SE[83]You should rest a little
longer.

\SE[47]Ronoa, please tell them... \SE[3]Thank you for helping me.
I don't hold any grudges. That's what she said...

\SE[50]... Me too. \SE[79] The fact that you all are alive is the
only salvation for me.
